                        <h3>Calculation Methods</h3>

                        <h4>Total Race Time Formula</h4>
                        <div class="tc-formula-box">
                            <strong>Total Time = Swim Time + T1 + Bike Time + T2 + Run Time</strong>
                        </div>

                        <h4>Performance Analysis</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Swim Pace:</strong> Swim Time √∑ Swim Distance (seconds per km)</li>
                            <li><strong>Bike Speed:</strong> Bike Distance √∑ Bike Time (km per hour)</li>
                            <li><strong>Run Pace:</strong> Run Time √∑ Run Distance (seconds per km)</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h4>Unit Conversions</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Distance:</strong> 1 mile = 1.60934 km | 1 km = 1000 m</li>
                            <li><strong>Speed:</strong> 1 km/h = 0.62137 mph | 1 m/s = 3.6 km/h</li>
                            <li><strong>Time:</strong> 1 hour = 3600 seconds | 1 minute = 60 seconds</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
